The CHIKV adaptation to 
 Aedes albopictus has constantly been associated to spread of CHIKF to new areas of the globe. In fact, full-length viral sequences unraveled unique adaptive variants in, at least, three occasions, that conferred selective advantage for CHIKV transmission by 
 Ae. albopictus (
 Tsetsarkin et al., 2007; 
 Beesoon et al., 2008; 
 De Lamballerie et al., 2008; 
 Dubrulle et al., 2009; 
 Severini et al., 2018).
